Obama Thanks Prince Charles for U.K. Assistance in Afghanistan

-- B y   K a t e   A n d e r s e n   B r o w e r
-- 
2011-05-05T00:04:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/obama-thanks-prince-charles-for-u-k-assistance-in-afghanistan.html
President  Barack Obama  thanked Prince Charles for contributions British troops are making in
Afghanistan and Libya and for his work on environmental issues
during a meeting at the White House today, according to an
administration statement.  The meeting affirmed “the strength and depth of the
alliance between the United States and the United Kingdom,” an
administration statement said. Obama is scheduled to make a
state visit to the U.K. at the end of the month.  Obama also congratulated him on the wedding of his son,
William, to the former  Kate Middleton  less than a week ago, an
event that was watched in about 18.6 million U.S. homes,
according to figures from  Nielsen Co.   Prince Charles , the first in line to the British throne,
arrived in the U.S. yesterday for a two-day visit to  Washington .
He toured the U.S. Supreme Court yesterday and visited an urban
farm in Washington, as part of his promotion of sustainable  food
production . Earlier today the heir to the throne delivered a
 keynote speech  on the matter at an agriculture conference at
Washington’s Georgetown University.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kate Andersen Brower in Washington at 
 kandersen7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
